events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 32 points and 14 rebounds and the Boston Celtics beat the San Antonio Spurs 116-103 on Wednesday night for their third straight victory and seventh in eight games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 32 points to help the Celtics beat Wemby and the Spurs, 116-103

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 24 points and eight rebounds and the Orlando Magic shook off a cold-shooting first half to beat the Charlotte Hornets 102-86 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero has 24 points and 8 rebounds as Orlando beats injury-riddled Charlotte 102-86

headlines.description: — Obi Toppin had season highs of 31 points and 10 rebounds, and the Indiana Pacers rallied from a 19-point deficit to beat the NBA-worst Washington Wizards 134-130 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Obi Toppin has 31 points, 10 rebounds as Pacers beat Wizards 134-130 in OT

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell had 22 points, five rebounds and four assists, and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Philadelphia 76ers 100-96 on Wednesday night in the teams' last game before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell scores 22 points as Nets beat 76ers 100-96

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson made the go-ahead jumper with 11.1 seconds left in overtime, Karl-Anthony Towns scored 44 points and the New York Knicks outlasted the Atlanta Hawks 149-148 on Wednesday night in a thrilling final game before the All-Star break for...
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson hits go-ahead jumper, Towns scores 44 points in Knicks' 149-148 OT win over Hawks

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 21 points and the East-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Toronto Raptors 131-108 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory and eighth in the last nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: East-leading Cavaliers rout Raptors 131-108 for 8th win in 9 games

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 29 points and the Detroit Pistons beat the Chicago Bulls 128-110 on Wednesday after dominating them the previous night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham scores 29 points and Pistons beat Bulls for second straight night, 128-110

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma had 19 points and 13 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks won without All-Stars Giannis Antetokounmpo and Damian Lillard, beating the Minnesota Timberwolves 103-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without Antetokounmpo and Lillard, the Bucks beat the Timberwolves 103-101

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Keon Ellis hit seven 3-pointers during a 27-point performance, Zach LaVine scored 20 of his 23 points in the second half, and the Sacramento Kings beat the New Orleans Pelicans 119-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ellis' 27 points off the bench helps the Kings hold on to beat Williamson and the Pelicans 119-111

events.name: Miami Heat at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 32 points and nine assists, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied from a 21-point deficit to defeat the Miami Heat 115-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 32, and the Thunder rally from 21 down to beat Heat 115-101

headlines.description: — Amen Thompson had 18 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds for his fourth career triple-double and the Houston Rockets used a big run late to get a 119-111 win over the Phoenix Suns Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amen Thompson's triple-double helps Rockets rally for 119-111 win over Suns

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored a career-high 55 points, Nikola Jokic had his 25th triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets beat the Portland Trail Blazers 132-121 on Wednesday night for their eighth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores career-high 55 points, Nuggets beat Trail Blazers 132-121 for 8th straight win

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 32 points and had a season-high three steals to lead the Utah Jazz to a 131-119 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen scores 32 points to lead Jazz past Lakers 131-119

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 42 points and took a charge in the closing seconds, Klay Thompson added 17 against his former team, and the undersized Dallas Mavericks beat the Golden State Warriors 111-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 42 points to lead Mavericks past Warriors 111-107

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 25 points, James Harden and Norman Powell each had 18 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 128-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard scores 25 points in Clippers' 128-114 victory over Grizzlies
